Explanation
- The class has @Path("/api/v0/ops/node") at the top; the method has @Path("/snapshots"), so the combined path is /api/v0/ops/node/snapshots.
- The source defines three methods that target that exact path:
  - getSnapshotDetails(...) is annotated with @GET and @Path("/snapshots") → GET is allowed.
  - takeSnapshot(...) is annotated with @POST and @Path("/snapshots") → POST is allowed.
  - clearSnapshots(...) is annotated with @DELETE and @Path("/snapshots") → DELETE is allowed.
- There is no @HEAD, @OPTIONS, @TRACE, @PUT, or @PATCH annotation for that path in the code, so those methods are not accepted according to the source.
- "All HTTP methods acceptable" is false because the code only exposes specific HTTP method handlers (GET, POST, DELETE) and there is no catch-all or annotation allowing every method.
